// pseudo-hook-check.sh
// Claude Code PostToolUse hook that intercepts Bash tool calls and triggers pseudo staleness tracking whenever a git commit is detected.
// synced: 2026-03-26T13:51:59Z

FUNCTION pseudo-hook-check [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: pseudo-track-commit (pseudo-track-commit)
  Registered in .claude/settings.json as a PostToolUse hook for the Bash tool. Receives tool input as JSON on stdin.
  Step 1. Read all of stdin into INPUT.
  Step 2. Parse INPUT as JSON using python3; extract the `command` field. If parsing fails, treat command as empty string.
  Step 3. IF the command matches the pattern `git commit` (word-boundary), resolve the script's own directory and call pseudo-track-commit.sh from the same directory.
  Step 4. ELSE do nothing and exit silently.
